maru for Debian
===============

This package provides the ConsenSys Maru Client (Validium/Prover Helper), packaged for Ethereum on ARM.

Services
--------

This package installs a systemd service, disabled by default:

- `maru.service`

To enable the service, run:
    sudo systemctl enable --now maru.service

Configuration
-------------

Configuration arguments are defined in the environment file:

- `/etc/ethereum/maru.conf`

You can edit this file to customize the `ARGS` variable passed to the binary.

Data Directories
----------------

By default, data is stored in the `ethereum` user's home directory.

User and Group
--------------

The service runs as the `ethereum` user and group.

